File: President Cyril Ramaphosa declared the state of disaster in March. JOHANNESBURG - The COVID-19 National State of Disaster will continue into next month. The Cabinet has approved the extension to 15 October. "This is to continue giving effect to the regulations that remain relevant to manage the spread of COVID-19 infections," Cabinet said in a statement. President Cyril Ramaphosa declared the state of disaster in March. READ: COVID-19 State of Disaster deadline looms Ramaphosa's announcement came with a travel ban on foreign nationals from high-risk countries such as Italy, Iran and China. At a meeting with the South African National Editor’s Forum this week, Ramaphosa hinted that there may soon be another adjustment of lockdown regulations. The president is expected to brief the nation next week.